EXAMPLE 2: How AI is Revolutionizing Customer Service

Completing a customer service request should be simple. For millions, it is slow and frustrating. The traditional call center experience relies on menus, queues, and repeated questions. It is outdated. Agentic AI fixes this.

The High Friction Service Process
A customer calls. He navigates an IVR menu. He waits on hold. When he reaches an agent, he repeats information he already provided. The agent asks for something he does not have. The call stalls. He hangs up or gives up.

A Broken Experience Creates Real Cost
The experience feels impersonal and inefficient. It erodes trust. For the business, the cost is high. Agents waste time on repetitive data collection. Abandonment rates rise. Errors increase. Records become inaccurate. Rework multiplies. Every minute spent on low value tasks is a minute not spent on complex needs or customer relationships.

An Intelligent Conversation, An Instant Outcome
Agentic automation changes this. A customer calls. Alice, an AI agent, greets him by name. She understands his intent. She guides the conversation. If he lacks a VIN, she adapts. She asks if he is near the vehicle. She gives him instructions to find the number. He provides it. She verifies details. She submits the proposal. A confirmation email arrives. The process is fully automated. The customer leaves satisfied.

Agentic AI in Action
Krista orchestrates this process.

Voice to Text and NLU transcribe and understand intent.
Agentic Orchestration manages the end to end workflow. It adapts when information is missing and guides the customer.
Generative AI creates the case record, writes notes, and sends the email.
Krista automates the entire event. Human agents focus on exceptions. Customers receive fast and accurate service.

