EXAMPLE 6: Elevate Recorded Meetings to Enterprise Knowledge

Teams record every meeting. Summaries scatter. Insights get lost. Decisions vanish. Recording tools capture words. They do not create knowledge. Meetings hold valuable insight that must be unified, not stored in isolation.

The Shortfall of Meeting Recordings
Zoom and Otter capture conversations. They generate summaries. The value stops there. Critical context disappears. Related emails, chats, and CRM entries remain disconnected. Teams waste time piecing together what happened.

Meetings as Enterprise Knowledge
Meetings belong to a larger data fabric. They sit next to emails, chats, documents, and system records. A meeting about a churn risk contains only part of the story. Emails contain the rest. Chats contain timelines. CRM contains value.

Unified, these pieces reveal patterns no summary can.

Unifying Knowledge with AI Led Management
